{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1972 | theme = | logo = | final = 12 February 1972 | presenters = [[Gunilla Marcus]] | winner = "[[Härliga sommardag]]" by [[Family Four]] | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Cirkus (Stockholm)|Cirkus]], [[Stockholm]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1972''' was the selection for the 13th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 12th time that this system of picking a song had been used. Approximately 1000 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Radio]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio.
