{{Infobox Convention | name = SugoiCon | logo = Sugoicon logo 2-3.png | logo_caption= SugoiCon logo. | status = On Hiatus | venue = Crowne Plaza Cincinnati North | location = [[Sharonville, Ohio]] | country = United States | first = 2000 | last = 2013 | organizer = Southwest Ohio Regional Animation<ref name="annwatanabe"/> | attendance = 1,400 in 2006 | activity = Video rooms, anime music video contest, masquerade, dance, dealer's room, panels, workshops, video game room, artist's alley, concert and karaoke | website = }}
'''SugoiCon''' was an annual three day [[anime convention]] in the [[Cincinnati–Northern Kentucky metropolitan area]] held at the Crowne Plaza Cincinnati North in [[Sharonville, Ohio]]. The convention was organized by Southwest Ohio Regional Animation.<ref name="annwatanabe">{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2010-07-22/shinichi-watanabe-appear-at-sugoicon | title = Shinichi Watanabe to Appear at Sugoicon | publisher = AnimeNewsNetwork | accessdate = 2012-11-22}}</ref>
==Programming== The convention typically featured an anime music video contest, concerts, costume contest, dealers room, game shows, guest panels, karaoke, masquerade, rave, video rooms, and workshops.<ref name="nky11">{{cite news | work = Gannett | title = Japanese animation convention returns | date = 2011-10-19 | url = http://cincinnati.com/blogs/kentoncountyconnects/2011/10/19/japanese-animation-convention-returns/ | first = Nancy | last = Daly | accessdate = 2012-11-22}}</ref><ref name="enquirer2003a">{{cite news | work = Gannett | title = Anime convention may draw 1,000 to N.Ky. | date = 2003-11-21 | url = http://www.enquirer.com/editions/2003/11/21/loc_anime21.html | first = Rebecca | last = Goodman| accessdate = 2012-11-22}}</ref><ref name="enquirer2003b">{{cite news | work = Gannett | title = Fans of anime gather to share their passion | date = 2003-11-23 | url = http://www.enquirer.com/editions/2003/11/23/loc_anime23.html | first = Liz| last = Oakes | accessdate = 2012-11-22}}</ref><ref name="newsrecord12">{{cite news | work = The News Record | title = SugoiCon Breaks Stereotypes | date = 2012-11-20 | url = http://www.newsrecord.org/college_living/article_2a8840d8-3390-11e2-b067-0019bb30f31a.html | first = Tyler | last = Bell | accessdate = 2012-11-22}}</ref> Due to scheduling problems, the 2014 event was cancelled.<ref name="AC-2014">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/5247/sugoicon-2014 | title = SugoiCon 2014 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2014-09-24}}</ref>
